IR:

* Iron Raptor could feel Prowl shifting on her back, and she had to admit it 
felt very strange.
Even in her other beast modes she had never had anyone ride on her back 
before...now she knew what a horse felt like.
By the tense feeling of Prowls muscles against her own she could feel that 
he was uncomfortable about something, maybe...ashamed?
But then again he did manage to crash into a tree and break his own wing, so 
she only guessed as much would be proper.

Iron Raptor looked over her black shoulder as Prowl spoke, seeing his repair 
system activate...but wondered just why he wasn't afraid of her...or even 
thought that she was disgusting by now.
All he ever showed was concern, and she guessed that it was right for him to 
feel that way. She would be the same if this was him instead of her. But 
then again, she wouldn't wish this on a Pred.
Well...maybe a Pred...

Iron Raptor turned her head back towards the direction of the Ark.
Hurry, that was what Prowl said...but she wondered if he could even hold on 
tight enough. Well...she could always find out.
It would be a long way too. There were a few gullies and fissures on the way 
there, but they should make it by nightfall if she ran all the way.
She growled at Prowl, in a slight sarcastic tone.*

" I suppose you want peanuts and complimentory drinks on this express 
transport as well...Sir?

* Then breaking into an easy trot before a smooth jog. She would wait until 
he was fully repaired before she ran out fully.*
